Domestic disappearance is a calculated residual, which indicates the amount of a commodity that is available for all uses in Canada. It does not represent total supplies of a commodity actually consumed by individuals. Food consumption data are available in CANSIM table 002-0010 and CANSIM table 002-0011.
Starting with reference month July 2018, imports and exports have been revised back to January 2011.
